### Request Flow: LLM Gateway

1. Client sends POST to `/api/llm/gateway` with `{ prompt_slug, variables }`
2. Middleware validates session via Supabase Auth
3. API checks user status is `approved` and role has LLM access
4. Loads prompt template from `prompt_templates` table by slug
5. Interpolates variables into the prompt template
6. Routes to the correct provider ({{#each providers_display}}{{this.id}}{{#unless @last}}, {{/unless}}{{/each}})
7. Calls provider API, streams or awaits response
8. Logs request to `llm_audit_log` (tokens, cost, latency, status)
9. Returns response to client

